data.name: label14.Text
data.value:
- 1st Option (ideal for multiple tests) Step 1: Click on the book Icon in the Main Menu (ideal for multiple tests), Step 2: Enter the step height, the date of the test and the tester's initials Step 3: Select or create a person Step 4: If the person's birth date was not indicated, indicate their current age Step 5: Record their heart rate after 2 minutes of effort, confirm, and so on until the system has enough to work with! Step 6: Enter possible comments and save the test!
- 2nd Option (ideal for a single test on a registered person) Step 1: Click on the Plus Icon at the end of a registered person's row Step 2: Enter the Step 2: Enter the step height, the date of the test and the tester's initials Step 4: If the person's birth date was not indicated, indicate their current age Step 5: Record their heart rate after 2 minutes of effort, confirm, and so on until the system has enough to work with! Step 6: Enter possible comments and save the test!

data.name: label17.Text
data.value: Step 1: In the main table, find the row of the person who took the test Step 2: Click on the Eye Icon, a menu of existing tests pops up Step 3: Click on the date corresponding to the test you want to view Step 4: View the test and if you want to delete it, click on the button on the bottom right

data.name: label15.Text
data.value:
- 1st Option (ideal to enter Step Test afterwards) Click on the Book Icon in the header of the Main Menu.
- 2nd Option (ideal to just register them for later) Click on the Person Icon in the header of the Main Menu.
